      <title outputclass="H3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">30.101</ph> Cost Accounting Standards.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d1869e13">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1883e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 15</xref>, Cost Accounting Standards, requires certain contractors and subcontractors to comply with Cost Accounting Standards (CAS) and to disclose in writing and follow consistently their cost accounting practices.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1883e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  Contracts that refer to this <xref href="FAR-i1087414.dita#i1087414"
                        base="i1087414"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  30</xref> for the purpose of applying the policies, procedures, standards and regulations promulgated by the CASB pursuant to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 15</xref>, shall be deemed to refer to the CAS, and any other regulations promulgated by the CASB (see 48 CFR Chapter99), all of which are hereby incorporated in this <xref href="FAR-i1087414.dita#i1087414"
                        base="i1087414"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  30</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1883e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  The <xref href="FAR-id1617M0V0RLG.dita#id1617M0V0RLG"
                        base="i999477"
                        outputclass="fm:TEXT"
                        class="- topic/xref "/> to the FAR loose-leaf edition contains-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d1869e55">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1883e59" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        Cost Accounting Standards and Cost Accounting Standards Board Rules and Regulations Recodified by the Cost Accounting Standards Board at 48 CFR Chapter99; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1883e68" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        The following preambles:</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol " id="d1869e74">
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1883e78" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              PartI-Preambles to the Cost Accounting Standards Published by the Cost Accounting Standards Board.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1883e87" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              PartII-Preambles to the Related Rules and Regulations Published by the Cost Accounting Standards Board.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li otherprops="i_ii_iii" outputclass="H7_i_ii_iii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1883e96" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              PartIII-Preambles Published under the FAR System.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1883e109" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  The preambles are not regulatory but are intended to explain why the Standards and related Rules and Regulations were written, and to provide rationale for positions taken relative to issues raised in the public comments. The preambles are printed in chronological order to provide an administrative history.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
